---
// "What is kiroxy" — pull-quote with a sidebar metric. Breaks the
// rhythm of (eyebrow + heading + cards) that every other section
// uses. Pure prose left, single hero number right.
---
<section id="what" aria-labelledby="what-title" class="alt">
  <div class="container what-grid">
    <div class="what-copy">
      <span class="eyebrow">what it is</span>
      <h2 id="what-title" class="big">A proxy, not a platform.</h2>
      <p class="prose">
        You have a Kiro subscription. You want Claude Code, Cursor,
        Continue, opencode, or any Anthropic-compatible client to use it
        without sending code through a third party.
        <span class="ink">kiroxy stands that endpoint up in five minutes.</span>
      </p>
      <p class="prose">
        It speaks the Anthropic Messages API and the OpenAI Chat
        Completions API on the inbound side, and routes to your own Kiro
        accounts on the outbound side. One Go binary. One config file.
        That's the product.
      </p>
    </div>

    <aside class="what-stat" aria-label="ratio of kiroxy to platform-sized alternatives">
      <div class="stat-group">
        <span class="stat-eyebrow">scope</span>
        <span class="stat-number">
          <span class="stat-num">22</span><span class="stat-unit">MiB</span>
        </span>
        <span class="stat-vs">vs</span>
        <span class="stat-compare">~250 MiB · LiteLLM stack</span>
        <span class="stat-compare">~700 MiB · Portkey stack</span>
      </div>

      <div class="stat-group">
        <span class="stat-eyebrow">deps</span>
        <span class="stat-number">
          <span class="stat-num">13</span><span class="stat-unit">direct deps</span>
        </span>
        <span class="stat-vs">vs</span>
        <span class="stat-compare">~80 · LiteLLM (pip)</span>
        <span class="stat-compare">~250 · Portkey (npm)</span>
      </div>

      <dl class="stat-grid">
        <div><dt>binary</dt><dd>one</dd></div>
        <div><dt>config</dt><dd>one</dd></div>
        <div><dt>deps</dt><dd>vendored</dd></div>
        <div><dt>egress</dt><dd>0 bytes</dd></div>
      </dl>

      <p class="stat-note">
        kiroxy ships as one binary because it does one thing.
        That's a feature, not a marketing line.
      </p>
    </aside>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .what-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.5fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
    gap: clamp(28px, 5vw, 80px);
    align-items: start;
  }
  @media (max-width: 880px) {
    .what-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: var(--sp-7); }
  }

  .eyebrow { margin-bottom: var(--sp-4); }

  .big {
    font-size: clamp(1.875rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);
    font-weight: var(--fw-medium);
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-6);
    color: var(--c-text);
    max-width: 22ch;
  }

  .prose {
    font-family: var(--font-text);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.5vw, 1.125rem);
    color: var(--c-text-dim);
    line-height: var(--lh-relaxed);
    max-width: 56ch;
  }
  .prose + .prose { margin-top: var(--sp-5); }
  .ink { color: var(--c-text); font-weight: var(--fw-medium); }

  /* ── Stat sidebar ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .what-stat {
    border-left: 1px solid var(--c-rule);
    padding-left: var(--sp-7);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-6);
    align-self: stretch;
    padding-top: var(--sp-3);
  }
  @media (max-width: 880px) {
    .what-stat {
      border-left: 0;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--c-rule);
      padding-left: 0;
      padding-top: var(--sp-7);
    }
  }
  .stat-group {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-3);
  }
  .stat-group:nth-child(2) .stat-num {
    color: var(--c-text);
  }
  .stat-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--fs-xs);
    color: var(--c-text-faint);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: var(--tr-caps);
    font-weight: var(--fw-medium);
  }
  .stat-number {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--sp-3);
  }
  .stat-num {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(3.25rem, 8vw, 5rem);
    font-weight: var(--fw-semibold);
    color: var(--c-accent);
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    line-height: 0.9;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }
  .stat-unit {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-md);
    color: var(--c-text-dim);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    font-feature-settings: "liga" 0, "calt" 0;
  }
  .stat-vs {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--fs-xs);
    color: var(--c-text-ghost);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: var(--tr-caps);
    margin-top: var(--sp-3);
  }
  .stat-compare {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    color: var(--c-text-faint);
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    font-feature-settings: "liga" 0, "calt" 0;
  }
  .stat-note {
    margin-top: var(--sp-5);
    font-family: var(--font-text);
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    color: var(--c-text-dim);
    line-height: var(--lh-relaxed);
    font-style: italic;
    max-width: 36ch;
  }

  /* ── Stat grid — diff-set from feature #6 bars ─────────────────── */
  .stat-grid {
    margin: var(--sp-5) 0 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: var(--sp-4);
    padding-top: var(--sp-5);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--c-rule);
  }
  .stat-grid > div {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-1);
    min-width: 0;
  }
  .stat-grid dt {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--c-text-faint);
    letter-spacing: var(--tr-caps);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-weight: var(--fw-medium);
  }
  .stat-grid dd {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-md);
    color: var(--c-text);
    font-feature-settings: "liga" 0, "calt" 0, "tnum";
  }

  /* ── Comparison bars (legacy — unused after bars removed) ───────── */
  .stat-bars {
    margin-top: var(--sp-5);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-3);
  }
  .bar-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 64px minmax(0, 1fr) 36px;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--sp-3);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-xs);
    color: var(--c-text-faint);
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    font-feature-settings: "liga" 0, "calt" 0, "tnum";
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }
  .bar-track {
    height: 6px;
    background: color-mix(in oklch, var(--c-rule), transparent 40%);
    border-radius: 1px;
    overflow: hidden;
    position: relative;
  }
  .bar-fill {
    display: block;
    height: 100%;
    background: var(--c-text-faint);
    border-radius: 1px;
  }
  .bar-fill-amb { background: var(--c-accent); }
  .bar-val { text-align: right; color: var(--c-text-dim); }
</style>
